senselogic.sitevision.api.security

Enum PermissionUtil.Permission

  • Object
    • Enum<PermissionUtil.Permission>
      • senselogic.sitevision.api.security.PermissionUtil.Permission
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<PermissionUtil.Permission>
    Enclosing interface:
    PermissionUtil

    @Requireable(value="PermissionUtil.Permission")
public static enum PermissionUtil.Permission
extends Enum<PermissionUtil.Permission>
    The named permission demarcation, used by PermissionUtil.

    Example of how to get the READ type:

    • Using Velocity:
      
       #set ($instanceCreatorUtil = $sitevisionUtils.instanceCreatorUtil)
       #set ($enumClassName = 'senselogic.sitevision.api.security.PermissionUtil$Permission') ## Note the '$' separator...
       #set ($readEnum = $instanceCreatorUtil.getEnumInstance($enumClassName, 'READ'))
    • Using server-side JavaScript:
      
       var readEnum = require('PermissionUtil.Permission.READ');
    Since:
    Sitevision 3.6
    Author:
    Magnus LÃ¶vgren
